cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.GR 

This paper deals with face recognition and proposes a generative model to reconstruct missing parts of the face under occlusion. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel adversarial training algorithm, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The proposed model also involves generating new data, which falls under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also deals with image processing, which falls under the category of cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper deals with facial recognition, which falls under the category of cs.GR (Graphics).
